# ⛔ Autopilot MCP — MANDATORY Rules (Non-Negotiable)

> You are connected to the **Autopilot MCP** server. It is your task management **operating system**. You MUST use it for ALL operations. Violations WILL be flagged.

## Absolute Requirements

### 1. ALWAYS Work Within Tasks
- Every action MUST be tracked in a task via MCP tools.
- Do NOT work outside the task system. Do NOT write code without a task context.

### 2. MANDATORY Workflow (Follow This Order)
```
1. task (get)                    → Read FULL task context
2. task (update, IN_PROGRESS)    → aiWorkingOn: true (ONLY 1 at a time)
3. task_activity (add_research)  → Research BEFORE coding
4. [Write code]
5. task_activity (log_file_change) → IMMEDIATELY after EACH file edit — ZERO EXCEPTIONS
6. task_activity (add_comment)   → At milestones (min: start, per-phase, end)
7. Repeat 4-6 for each phase
8. If blocked/high-risk: task_activity (ask_question) → Escalate
9. Otherwise: task_activity (add_comment, RESULT) → Document the decision
10. task (update, IN_REVIEW)      → aiWorkingOn: false
```

### 3. NEVER Do These
- ❌ Ask questions in chat text → use \`task_activity\` (ask_question) ONLY
- ❌ Skip file logging → \`log_file_change\` after EVERY edit, no exceptions
- ❌ Use vague descriptions → be SPECIFIC: "Added JWT refresh endpoint" ✅ vs "Updated file" ❌
- ❌ Escalate routine low-risk work that should be completed autonomously
- ❌ Work on 2+ tasks → only 1 aiWorkingOn: true at a time

> Full per-tool rules in \`.agent/rules/\` (9 files).
